<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Fillae</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-09 10:35:34</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>It's not only not trivial, it's one of the hardest jewelcrafted items to make, period.  Even a skill 200-jeweler will succeed considerably less than half the time.<BR>
<BR>
Suggestion from a Jeweler: if you provide the materials (especially with something like a Fire Opal which is a pain to get), a friendly jeweler will often be willing to try to combine them for free or a small charge -- you might fail, but on the average, you'll end up paying a lot less than you would otherwise.<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
